WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.800
Welcome back to Mental Fitness. We're gonna talk about goal setting this week.

00:10.800 --> 00:16.400
Goal setting is such an important part of accomplishing our tasks and our goals

00:16.400 --> 00:21.520
and our writing. Whether it's small or large, goal setting is such an important

00:21.520 --> 00:27.960
tool to use intentionally. So get your notebooks out and get writing as we're

00:28.000 --> 00:34.920
gonna set some goals for this year. No matter if you're setting long-term or

00:34.920 --> 00:39.320
short-term goals, big or small goals, you want to ask yourself some questions

00:39.320 --> 00:44.240
about them so that your mindset is in the right space to accomplish them.

00:44.240 --> 00:49.120
Firstly, we want to ask ourselves why are we motivated to accomplish this goal.

00:49.120 --> 00:54.680
Write down your reasons why the goal is a must and summarize it into two

00:54.680 --> 01:00.640
sentences so that you can memorize it and keep it in your mind at all times. In

01:00.640 --> 01:07.640
order to accomplish something, it needs to be on the front of our mind. Next, we

01:07.640 --> 01:12.640
want to envision our outcome. I want you to close your eyes and actually envision

01:12.640 --> 01:18.720
exactly how it would feel, how it looks, who is there when the goal is

01:18.720 --> 01:22.680
accomplished. And I want you to write down your ideal outcome for the

01:22.680 --> 01:28.880
situation or the goal. Whether it's very small and just for today or very large

01:28.880 --> 01:34.520
and it's going to take multiple years, write it down and be very specific. Who

01:34.520 --> 01:39.880
is involved, what people are involved, what resources are involved, and envision

01:39.880 --> 01:49.840
it to its fullest extent. Now you're ready to start planning for your goal. So

01:49.880 --> 01:57.560
first of all, give yourself a time frame, an exact time frame, a deadline and stick

01:57.560 --> 02:03.040
to it with no excuses. This is the most important part of the planning stage of

02:03.040 --> 02:08.400
goal setting. Make sure you give yourself a deadline. Write it down and put it

02:08.400 --> 02:12.600
wherever you need to in your house, on your devices, and make sure you

02:12.600 --> 02:18.680
accomplish a portion of that goal by that date exactly the way that you set

02:18.680 --> 02:23.880
out to do. Write your why at the top of the plan so that you know where your

02:23.880 --> 02:29.720
motivation is coming from and you'll have the energy to complete the task. Be

02:29.720 --> 02:35.440
very specific with your planning. What will you be doing daily to accomplish

02:35.440 --> 02:41.360
this goal? Who will be involved? What are their exact roles? How much exact money

02:41.360 --> 02:47.160
do you need? How much exact time do you need? How much exact energy do you need?

02:47.200 --> 02:52.880
Write this all down and be very specific to each goal. Like I said, even if it's a

02:52.880 --> 02:59.080
daily goal, if it's a yearly goal, if it's a monthly goal, write it down and be

02:59.080 --> 03:03.360
very specific. The more we dwell on the things that are going to bring us life,

03:03.360 --> 03:12.640
the more life will come into our life. The journey of a thousand miles starts

03:12.680 --> 03:20.440
with one step. So step every single day. You have a categorized list here. Start

03:20.440 --> 03:24.360
with your why. Get a good vision and plan to get there.

